# Phase 1: Browser Control — Implementation Plan

## Context

Phase 0 delivered: 13 crates compile green, proto frozen, gRPC contract defined. But every type is a stub — `CdpBackend;`, `ChromiumProcess;`, `IpcServer;`. Phase 1 makes them real.

**Deliverable:** "Chromium launches, navigates, interacts via gRPC."

**Quality bar:** Production infrastructure — RAII process cleanup, typed CDP commands, proper error handling, zero unwrap() in library code.

---

## Architecture

```
ans-daemon (main.rs)
├── Loads ans.toml config
├── Starts IpcServer (gRPC on loopback:50051)
└── On shutdown: graceful drain

IpcServer (ans-ipc/server.rs)
├── Implements tonic-generated AgentNervousSystem service
├── Owns SessionManager (Arc<RwLock<HashMap<Uuid, SessionHandle>>>)
├── gRPC methods delegate to SessionManager → CdpBackend
└── Health RPC returns system status

SessionManager (new: ans-ipc/src/session.rs)
├── create(goal_id, start_url) → spawns ChromiumProcess, wraps in CdpBackend
├── close(session_id) → kills Chromium, removes from map
├── execute(session_id, action) → dispatches to CdpBackend method
└── tracks: session→backend mapping, status, goal_id

CdpBackend (ans-cdp/src/client.rs)
├── Implements BrowserBackend trait
├── Owns ChromiumProcess + tokio_tungstenite WebSocket
├── Sends CDP commands, awaits responses via oneshot channels
├── Background task reads WS messages, routes to waiting commands/event handlers
└── Implements reconnect with exponential backoff

ChromiumProcess (ans-cdp/src/process.rs)
├── Finds chromium/chrome on PATH
├── Spawns headless Chromium with remote-debugging-port
├── Discovers WS debug URL from /json/version
├── Drop impl kills child process (RAII guarantee)
└── Health: periodic Browser.getVersion ping

CdpCommand (ans-cdp/src/command.rs)
├── CdpCommand { id, method, params }
├── CdpResponse { id, result, error }
├── Typed builders for Page, DOM, Runtime, Input domains
└── Response parsers return domain types
```

