## File-by-File Implementation

### 1. `crates/ans-cdp/src/process.rs` — Chromium lifecycle

**ChromiumProcess struct:**
```rust
pub struct ChromiumProcess {
    child: Mutex<Option<Child>>,  // tokio::process::Child
    debug_port: u16,
    debug_url: String,            // ws://localhost:{port}/devtools/browser/{id}
    user_data_dir: PathBuf,       // cleaned up on drop
}
```

**Methods:**
- `pub async fn launch() -> Result<Self>` — find exe, pick port, spawn, fetch debug URL
- `pub fn debug_url(&self) -> &str`
- `pub fn debug_port(&self) -> u16`

**Drop impl:** Kill child process, clean up `user_data_dir`. Fire warning if child was still running (should have been closed explicitly).

**Port allocation:** Bind `TcpListener::bind("127.0.0.1:0")` → read local addr → drop listener → pass port to chromium. This avoids port collisions without a port manager.

**Chromium discovery:** Try `chromium`, `chromium-browser`, `chrome`, `google-chrome`. On Windows also check `%LOCALAPPDATA%\Chromium\Application\chrome.exe` and `%ProgramFiles%\Google\Chrome\Application\chrome.exe`.

**Spawn args:**
```
--headless=new
--no-sandbox
--disable-gpu
--disable-dev-shm-usage
--disable-extensions
--disable-background-networking
--remote-debugging-port={port}
--user-data-dir={temp_dir}
--window-size=1280,720
about:blank
```

**Debug URL discovery:** HTTP GET `http://127.0.0.1:{port}/json/version` → parse JSON → extract `webSocketDebuggerUrl` field. Retry with backoff (Chromium takes time to start).

