### 7. `crates/ans-ipc/src/arrow_ipc.rs` — Arrow IPC (basic)

Extend beyond `shm_dir()`:

```rust
pub struct IpcBuffer {
    path: PathBuf,
    key: String,  // random unique key
}

impl IpcBuffer {
    pub fn create(prefix: &str) -> Result<Self>
    pub fn write_arrow_batch(&self, schema: &Schema, batch: &RecordBatch) -> Result<()>
    pub fn read_arrow_batch(&self) -> Result<RecordBatch>
    pub fn key(&self) -> &str
    pub fn path(&self) -> &Path
}

impl Drop for IpcBuffer {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        let _ = std::fs::remove_file(&self.path);
    }
}
```

Use `arrow::ipc::writer::FileWriter` and `arrow::ipc::reader::FileReader` — the file-based IPC format suits our mmap approach. The gRPC message carries the `key` string; the receiver opens the file at `shm_dir()/ans_{key}.arrow`.

### 8. `crates/ans-daemon/src/main.rs` — Entry point

```rust
use clap::Parser;

#[derive(Parser)]
#[command(name = "ans-daemon")]
struct Cli {
    #[arg(long, default_value = "ans.toml")]
    config: PathBuf,
    
    #[arg(long, default_value = "50051")]
    grpc_port: u16,
}

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() -> Result<()> {
    color_eyre::install()?;
    
    let cli = Cli::parse();
    
    // Load config
    let config = load_config(&cli.config)?;
    
    // Init tracing
    tracing_subscriber::fmt()
        .with_env_filter("ans=debug,info")
        .init();
    
    tracing::info!("ans-daemon v{} starting", env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION"));
    
    // Create IPC server
    let server = IpcServer::new();
    let addr = SocketAddr::new(IpAddr::V4(Ipv4Addr::LOCALHOST), cli.grpc_port);
    
    tracing::info!("gRPC server listening on {}", addr);
    
    // Graceful shutdown
    server.serve(addr).await?;
    
    Ok(())
}
```

**Signal handling:** `tokio::signal::ctrl_c()` → initiate graceful shutdown. On SIGTERM: close all sessions (kills all Chromium processes), then stop gRPC server.

